ROMPINGLY
Romp"ing*ly, adv.

Defn: In a romping manner.

ROMPISH
Romp"ish, a.

Defn: Given to rude play; inclined to romp. --- Romp"ish, adv.
 -- Romp"ish*ness, n.

ROMPU
Rom"pu, a. Etym: [F. rompu, p. p. of rompre to breeak, L. rumpere.
See Rupture.] (Her.)

Defn: Broken, as an ordinary; cut off, or broken at the top, as a
